Hands down this was Furiosa from Mad Max Fury Road. It was made under a fairly tight timeline (for me anyway) and right in the middle of a move from one state to another which added to the challenge. I saw the movie opening day and by 5pm that evening I had shaved my head and was prepared to make this journey. The research and material sourcing on this was pretty endless.
â–ªï¸
This costume had so many different elements to it that even when breaking them down into sections it felt overwhelming. Never before have I made something so deceptively complex and challenging. Several times I thought I might not actually get it done before Dragoncon. There were many meltdowns ğŸ˜‚. 
â–ªï¸
I took over 600 screenshots and did so much research before and during the build for this. Every little piece of her costume I studied and tried to get right. I think I mostly succeeded even though I would definitely do some things differently if I were to make her arm again.
â–ªï¸
